and you want to be found out.

19:21.451 --> 19:24.579
There's this psychological mechanism
according to which...

19:24.705 --> 19:27.832
serial-killers do all they can
to get found out.

19:27.958 --> 19:31.085
Let's do. We can stop if we get bored.

19:31.211 --> 19:36.549
Yes, it's like when we played
truth or dare as kids.

19:36.717 --> 19:41.053
So what? We used to jerk off
together as kids too.

19:41.430 --> 19:44.932
- I didn't jerk off with you.
- No, you did it alone.

19:45.684 --> 19:48.477
- Cosimo, put your phone on the table.
- Huh?

19:48.604 --> 19:50.605
Get your phone out.

19:54.985 --> 19:59.071
- Should I be worried?
- No! Of course not!

19:59.948 --> 20:03.075
Here you go, it's not a problem.

20:03.619 --> 20:05.828
Are we really doing this?

20:05.954 --> 20:08.873
It's rude to keep phones
on the table while eating.

20:09.708 --> 20:14.503
- Yes, Diego always switched his off.
- Lele leaves his face down.

20:17.633 --> 20:19.759
- What?
- You leave it face down.

20:19.885 --> 20:22.094
Think I haven't noticed?

20:23.722 --> 20:26.974
It's not intentional.
I pull out my phone and place it down.

20:27.100 --> 20:30.102
If you scratch the screen
it costs 200 euros to replace it.

20:30.270 --> 20:33.022
- 50 in Chinatown.
- Let's scratch it then.

20:34.733 --> 20:38.527
Look here, look...
I'll put it face up.

20:39.112 --> 20:41.781
I'll get mine.
But I'm warning you...

20:41.990 --> 20:46.535
- If mom calls, I'm not answering.
- If the allergic dog client calls,

20:46.662 --> 20:49.914
I'm not answering it,
otherwise it's all yours.

20:50.040 --> 20:54.794
- Come on, let's see what happens.
- You do agree this is really stupid?

20:55.170 --> 20:59.131
- It's really stupid.
- Fucking stupid, come on, guys!

20:59.549 --> 21:00.549
Dad?

21:01.009 --> 21:03.135
- Sofia.
- Hi, Sofia!

21:03.262 --> 21:06.055
- Hello, everyone.
- She gets prettier every day.

21:07.015 --> 21:09.892
- She takes after her mother.
- Can you come here?

21:10.143 --> 21:11.811
Excuse me.

21:14.523 --> 21:17.024
Can I have some money, please?

21:17.943 --> 21:22.571
- Why didn't you ask in there?
- Not in front of mom.

21:24.074 --> 21:26.575
- What happened?
- The usual.

21:26.952 --> 21:28.786
You argued?

21:28.954 --> 21:31.831
- How old is Sofia?
- 17 in June.

21:31.957 --> 21:35.584
I remember when we celebrated
her birthday in Circeo.

21:35.711 --> 21:38.462
- She was 10, right?
- Yes, 10.

21:38.714 --> 21:40.589
- Seems like yesterday.
- Great...

21:40.716 --> 21:44.176
"Time flies by so fast!"
has been said.

21:44.553 --> 21:47.054
- "This used to be a farm..."
- "All Blacks have rhythm."

21:47.222 --> 21:49.849
Don't forget
"Pippo Baudo is very professional".

21:49.975 --> 21:53.477
- That's enough, guys.
- Hold it, first text.

21:53.729 --> 21:55.938
- It's mine.
- Shall we read it?

21:56.064 --> 21:57.606
Yes.

21:59.985 --> 22:03.112
"I want your body"?
Who's it from?

22:03.238 --> 22:06.365
- I don't know.
- We're off to a good start.

22:06.616 --> 22:07.992
What does it mean?

22:08.118 --> 22:09.744
- I don't know.
- Who sent it?

22:09.953 --> 22:12.121
The number's not in my phone,
I don't know.

22:12.873 --> 22:15.624
Must be the wrong number,
I don't know.

22:15.751 --> 22:18.002
What do I do?

22:19.755 --> 22:24.258
- It's the number from the text.
- Answer it.

22:24.885 --> 22:27.720
- Answer it.
- Yeah, right.

22:28.764 --> 22:31.640
- Put it on speaker.
- Yes. Take it easy.

22:31.767 --> 22:35.269
I'll put it on speaker.
Hello? Who is it?

22:39.274 --> 22:41.025
Hello?

22:42.277 --> 22:45.029
No answer...

22:45.614 --> 22:48.032
Hello? Who's that?
Who is it?

22:48.784 --> 22:50.368
It's fucking me.

22:54.664 --> 22:57.750
- What is wrong with you?
- It was a joke.

22:57.918 --> 23:00.127
- Fuck off!
- What kind of joke is that?

23:00.295 --> 23:03.381
- You're such a...
- He's a loser.

23:03.757 --> 23:05.257
- You're a loser.
- Really.

23:05.801 --> 23:09.303
- Just playing around.
- I knew it was a joke.

23:09.805 --> 23:12.306
- Go fuck yourself!
- Bullshit!

23:15.894 --> 23:17.895
Give me my phone, I'm going out.

23:18.021 --> 23:19.939
- Say bye at least.
- Bye.

23:20.273 --> 23:21.941
- Bye, Sofia.
- Bye, Sofia.

23:22.067 --> 23:25.778
- I said hello to them before.
- She said hello before.

23:28.198 --> 23:31.200
- She's not always like that.
- She's often worse.

23:31.326 --> 23:33.411
They're unbearable at that age.

23:33.703 --> 23:36.080
- What were you like at her age?
- Me?

23:37.416 --> 23:39.959
- What was he like?
- I remember what he was like.

23:41.086 --> 23:44.213
He was... help me out.

23:44.798 --> 23:46.799
Superficial.

23:47.968 --> 23:51.971
Perfect adjective. He only loved
soccer and something else.

23:52.097 --> 23:55.307
- Don't listen to him, darling.
- His mom was desperate.

23:55.684 --> 23:57.726
- Distraught.
- Whereas their mothers were happy.

23:58.353 --> 24:01.063
I'm not sure I'd be a good mother.

24:01.356 --> 24:04.942
- Why, are you pregnant?
- No, no...

24:05.110 --> 24:07.111
Are you trying?

24:09.865 --> 24:12.491
- You could say that.
- Congratulations then!

24:13.076 --> 24:15.870
There's nothing to celebrate yet.

24:15.996 --> 24:19.373
Well, at least someone's screwing!

24:19.875 --> 24:22.877
We haven't even eaten
the first course yet, easy!

24:23.003 --> 24:26.088
What's the big deal?
Nobody here would be shocked.

24:26.256 --> 24:27.214
So?

24:27.382 --> 24:32.261
After all these years of marriage,
no one screws like in the early days.

24:32.387 --> 24:35.389
They're trying for a baby,
it's not...

24:35.765 --> 24:39.894
A more sober toast then. To children
and the meaning they give our lives.

24:40.020 --> 24:42.897
Bummer,
I preferred the screwing toast.

24:43.023 --> 24:45.274
Peppe, you're never satisfied.

24:45.484 --> 24:50.488
I don't like this idea that life has
no meaning if you don't have kids.

24:50.780 --> 24:54.783
- It's sometimes a convenient decision.
- What do you mean?

24:55.410 --> 25:00.998
You have a kid, get on with life
and think of nothing else.

25:01.249 --> 25:05.169
- I don't want a kid just to do that.
- Why else then?

25:05.378 --> 25:07.796
- For a thousand reasons.
- Give me one.

25:08.006 --> 25:11.425
- One. To complete the couple.
- For example.

25:11.801 --> 25:15.930
So two people can't be happy
without depending on someone else.

25:16.014 --> 25:19.266
- You're a pain!
- The other day we argued about God.

25:19.392 --> 25:23.312
It's the same thing in the end.
I don't want their help.

25:23.396 --> 25:26.148
I want to be
the meaning of my own life.

25:26.274 --> 25:29.818
I'm selfish and I'll die selfish.
Cheers.

25:30.445 --> 25:33.322
Sometimes having children
can be selfish.

25:34.157 --> 25:40.037
- Why selfish?
- It's a generous act, isn't it?

25:40.205 --> 25:43.457
No, sometimes it can just be
the fear of growing old.

25:43.792 --> 25:46.794
Many hope a child
can give them a second life.

25:46.920 --> 25:50.965
I don't torment myself about it.
I've enjoyed having a daughter.

25:51.091 --> 25:54.218
I agree with Rocco.
You can make fun of me,

25:54.344 --> 25:57.846
but the best moment of the day
is when I put Rosa to bed.

25:57.973 --> 26:02.977
She looks at me and says I'm so
beautiful. That makes me happy...

26:03.353 --> 26:07.064
- Happy, happy...
- We get the message, you're happy.

26:07.190 --> 26:10.109
- Did she say "happy"?
- There was an echo.

26:10.235 --> 26:15.239
We'll talk again when she's 16
and tells you to piss off.

26:15.448 --> 26:20.619
Don't say that, and it's true,
kids give you a second chance.

26:20.996 --> 26:24.331
It's like going over your life
again through them.

26:24.457 --> 26:28.335
You see, I don't want
to go over my life again.

26:28.461 --> 26:32.381
Because you had a shitty life.
I wasn't joking.

26:34.843 --> 26:37.136
- It's my sister, what do I do?
- Answer it.

26:38.221 --> 26:40.222
- Put it on speaker.
- Hi, Marta.

26:40.390 --> 26:42.891
- Peppe, the speaker.
- Wait a minute.

26:45.145 --> 26:46.520
- Hi.
- Hi.

26:46.896 --> 26:50.899
- Careful, you're on speaker.
- That's not fair!

26:51.026 --> 26:54.153
- Speaker?
- Yes, you're on speaker.

26:54.279 --> 26:57.531
- You can't tell her.
- Turn it off.

26:57.866 --> 27:00.159
- I can't.
- Why not?

27:00.285 --> 27:03.162
- I just can't, Marta.
- What's all that noise?

27:03.288 --> 27:06.040
- I'm at Rocco and Eva's.
- Game over.

27:06.249 --> 27:10.044
- Hello, Marta.
- Hello, everyone. Okay...

27:10.295 --> 27:14.048
- I'll call back.
- I'm not going to Anzio, got it?

27:14.257 --> 27:16.675
We'll talk about it tomorrow. Bye.

27:18.928 --> 27:21.930
- Sorry, I messed up.
- You messed up?

27:22.057 --> 27:24.683
I wasn't ready.
I'll get it right next time.

27:25.310 --> 27:28.395
- What was that about Anzio?
- My sister found me a job

27:28.521 --> 27:30.314
in a private school.

27:30.440 --> 27:32.941
- Why not go?
- It's too far away.

27:33.151 --> 27:38.072
- You can't be picky these days.
- It'd be nice to work at the seaside.

27:38.198 --> 27:40.908
I'd jump at the chance
to move to Anzio.

27:43.578 --> 27:45.287
What was that?

27:45.455 --> 27:48.082
- You'd jump at the chance to move...
- To Anzio.

27:49.084 --> 27:50.959
Yes, why not?

27:51.086 --> 27:53.921
You'd move to Anzio tomorrow?

27:54.089 --> 27:58.342
- Tomorrow, you'd move...
- She heard. We said it three times.

27:58.468 --> 28:02.429
Okay, I only said it
to encourage Peppe.

28:02.597 --> 28:06.100
- He's not a kid, you know.
- I've sent my resume everywhere.

28:06.434 --> 28:10.229
- Something will turn up.
- It doesn't work that way.

28:10.355 --> 28:14.233
- Am I on trial?
- Anyway, they can't fire you like that.

28:14.359 --> 28:18.320
They didn't, they just didn't renew
my contract, it's different.

28:18.613 --> 28:23.242
It's worse. You've had a temporary
contract for the last 10 years.

28:23.451 --> 28:28.497
- It's illegal, you could sue.
- Thanks, but I don't need help.

28:28.623 --> 28:32.626
I want to solve this on my own,
without any pressure.

28:32.877 --> 28:36.255
- And without going to Anzio.
- That's right, take your time...

28:36.589 --> 28:39.508
- Peppe, get a fucking move on!
- That's enough!

28:40.093 --> 28:45.723
As soon as I shut the shop,
I bought a taxi.

28:46.224 --> 28:50.018
- Let's follow his example!
- Joke all you want.

28:50.145 --> 28:53.522
I'm moving ahead,
I've put my taxi license up for sale.

28:54.357 --> 28:57.651
- You haven't started paying for it yet.
- You're selling it?

28:57.986 --> 29:01.238
- I want to see what it's worth.
- When were you going to tell me?

29:01.406 --> 29:03.741
- I was going to.
- When?

29:04.033 --> 29:07.119
- It's only an idea, it's not...
- As usual.

29:07.662 --> 29:11.039
- This time it's the right decision.
- It always is.

29:11.624 --> 29:15.669
Guys, the world's changing fast.
Car2go, car-sharing...

29:15.795 --> 29:19.798
Uber. Ever heard of them?
Taxis will be extinct soon.

29:20.175 --> 29:23.677
- So I'm looking to the future.
- Like with e-cigarettes.

29:25.388 --> 29:30.392
- He had bad luck that time.
- I blame the tobacco lobby.

29:30.518 --> 29:35.063
They financed the revolution
in Nicaragua.

29:35.273 --> 29:40.068
- Which is situated exactly...
- I'll tell you later where it is.

29:40.278 --> 29:43.322
- But at least I tried.
- Like when you bred Yorkshires.

29:46.075 --> 29:48.076
You're indefensible.

29:48.203 --> 29:50.454
Were Lady and the Tramp
to blame that time?

29:51.039 --> 29:52.456
Come on...

29:52.582 --> 29:54.792
Pass me that plate?

29:57.337 --> 30:02.090
- You baked the zucchini flowers?
- Did you want them fried? Lele!

30:06.471 --> 30:09.181
- Did you get your license back?
- No.

30:09.599 --> 30:13.727
- Not until the trial is over.
- When's the hearing?

30:14.729 --> 30:17.356
- At the end of June.
- Are you worried?

30:18.316 --> 30:21.568
No, just tired.
I can't wait until it's all over.

30:22.737 --> 30:26.615
- Is everything sorted?
- The lawyer says I'll be cleared.

30:26.741 --> 30:28.492
We'll celebrate this summer then.

30:29.828 --> 30:31.620
Who is it?

30:33.206 --> 30:35.123
It's dad.

30:35.375 --> 30:37.501
- Zucchini flowers...
- I'm famished.

30:37.627 --> 30:39.628
- Sit down.
- Put it on speaker.

30:42.632 --> 30:45.634
- Hi, dad.
- Hello, darling, how are you?

30:45.760 --> 30:49.012
- Fine, I've got friends for dinner.
- I won't keep you then.

30:49.222 --> 30:52.599
I spoke to Blanchard, he said
you can have the operation in Rome.

30:52.767 --> 30:55.727
He comes down twice a month
to the Quisisana Clinic.

30:56.104 --> 30:58.146
I'll send you his number,
call him.

30:58.273 --> 31:01.358
Thanks, dad, bye.
Say hello to mom.

31:02.861 --> 31:07.531
- What operation is that?
- It's nothing serious.

31:09.534 --> 31:12.160
Augmentation mammoplasty.

31:16.165 --> 31:18.292
I'm getting a boob job.

31:18.668 --> 31:20.377
- A boob job?
- Yes.

31:20.753 --> 31:23.422
- Why didn't you tell me?
- You're a therapist!

31:23.631 --> 31:26.550
- So what?
- Therapists don't get boob jobs.

31:26.801 --> 31:30.679
- It does seem strange.
- Why? I don't like my boobs.

31:31.389 --> 31:37.185
- You should make yourself like them.
- Therapists should accept themselves.

31:37.645 --> 31:41.398
A woman who has a boob job
doesn't accept herself?

31:42.692 --> 31:44.526
No.

31:46.195 --> 31:50.324
- I accept everything but my boobs.
- Let Rocco do it.

31:50.533 --> 31:53.285
- Why don't you do it?
- Why don't I do it?

31:53.453 --> 31:55.579
Because her consultant father said no.

31:56.789 --> 32:01.585
Only the best for his daughter.
Dr. Blanchard, a VIP surgeon

32:01.836 --> 32:07.299
who operates in Italy, but lives
in Switzerland. Not Rocco Buccilli.

32:07.467 --> 32:11.178
Who does boob and ass jobs
for cashiers and secretaries.

32:11.304 --> 32:14.348
I do two for one:
two boobs for the price of one.

32:15.808 --> 32:17.684
- Are you done?
- It's true.

32:17.852 --> 32:20.354
- No.
- Then enlighten me.

32:21.230 --> 32:23.941
A husband can't do
his wife's boob job.

32:24.233 --> 32:26.443
It's a matter of common sense.

32:26.611 --> 32:28.946
You'd lose all sexual attraction.

32:29.364 --> 32:32.824
- I agree with Eva.
- The cook never feels like eating.

32:32.992 --> 32:35.744
- That's a good one.
- He does it all the time.

32:35.870 --> 32:38.747
He says, "You know what?
You eat it all!"

32:38.873 --> 32:42.250
This is the official reason,
her father considers me an idiot.

32:42.752 --> 32:46.213
- That's not true.
- He wanted a heart surgeon for her.

32:46.339 --> 32:50.217
- A luminary like himself.
- That's enough.

32:50.385 --> 32:55.472
Why don't you let Blanchard do one
boob, and your husband the other?

32:55.640 --> 32:58.517
- Without knowing which one.
- Then decide which is better.

32:58.768 --> 33:03.355
No, get daddy to decide:
"Dad, which is Blanchard's boob?"

33:04.399 --> 33:08.860
I really shouldn't say this,
but she doesn't need it.

33:09.362 --> 33:13.240
- He paid you a compliment.
- It must be the eclipse.

33:13.408 --> 33:16.660
Eva's right, it's like you
going to her for therapy.

33:20.289 --> 33:22.290
It's unthinkable, right?

33:22.542 --> 33:27.546
You don't get it, it would be
unthinkable for him to go to therapy!

33:27.755 --> 33:32.551
I'm put off by how long it takes,
but I'd like to try.

33:32.677 --> 33:36.430
You're good at sitting
on a sofa for hours!

33:36.514 --> 33:39.683
You're a real comedian tonight!

33:39.809 --> 33:44.646
This need to talk about
my private business to a stranger...

33:44.772 --> 33:48.442
No offense Eva,
but it's not for me.

33:48.568 --> 33:50.902
You can talk to friends instead.

33:51.320 --> 33:54.448
- I have him...
- And it's free too.

33:54.657 --> 33:59.327
He won't go because he thinks
therapy is a waste of time.

33:59.537 --> 34:03.582
Admit it, I won't be offended.
You think my job is a waste of time.

34:03.791 --> 34:06.835
- Why do you say that?
- Because it's what you think.

34:06.961 --> 34:10.297
I don't, I think we do
very similar jobs.

34:10.465 --> 34:13.467
You do brain jobs, I do boob jobs.
We make people feel better,

34:13.592 --> 34:17.344
it's just that you take years,
and I take a few hours.

34:19.681 --> 34:21.433
- Whose is that?
- Not mine.

34:21.601 --> 34:23.351
- Not mine.
- Calm down.

34:23.561 --> 34:25.937
- It's the gnocchi.
- I'll go.

34:26.731 --> 34:29.608
- Hand me your plates.
- Thanks, Carlotta.

34:31.985 --> 34:34.112
- I'll go smoke.
- I'll come with you.

34:44.456 --> 34:48.085
- What's the moon like?
- It's partly covered.

34:52.090 --> 34:55.342
- Peppe, I've got a problem.
- What kind?

34:57.011 --> 34:59.387
Well...

34:59.514 --> 35:02.724
every night at 10:00
a friend of mine...

35:03.643 --> 35:06.520
- She sends me...
- A goodnight kiss?

35:07.396 --> 35:10.524
Sort of.
She sends me a photo.

35:12.401 --> 35:14.653
- She sends you a photo!
- A photo.

35:14.779 --> 35:16.780
What kind of photo?

35:16.906 --> 35:18.740
A photo of herself.

35:21.410 --> 35:23.662
You're in trouble.

35:23.913 --> 35:25.997
I need you to help me out.

35:27.166 --> 35:31.795
- How can I help you?
- We have the same phone.

35:32.421 --> 35:34.923
We'll swap them,
just until the photo arrives.

35:35.049 --> 35:38.176
- Then I'll receive the photo. Come on!
- But you're single.

35:38.553 --> 35:40.762
No, pal, not any more.

35:40.888 --> 35:42.931
Okay, but Lucilla's
not here with you tonight.

35:43.057 --> 35:46.560
- You could have refused to play.
- I'm in the shit. Help!

35:46.686 --> 35:48.562
No, I don't want to.

35:48.688 --> 35:52.691
Do you want all hell to break loose
for something so petty?

35:53.818 --> 35:57.445
Peppe doesn't want to
so he'll ruin an entire family.

36:06.038 --> 36:09.666
And what kind of photos
are you talking about?

36:09.792 --> 36:14.337
- Just an ordinary photo.
- Don't show me up, or else...

36:14.547 --> 36:19.050
Peppe, two nights ago she sent me
a photo of her in Pluto pajamas.

36:20.553 --> 36:22.846
- You see...
- Pluto?

36:22.972 --> 36:25.432
- Pluto.
- How old is she?

36:27.101 --> 36:29.060
I don't know.

36:32.481 --> 36:35.984
- Are you going to help me or not?
- What a pain!

36:41.199 --> 36:44.743
I'm not sure I should tell you,
but your husband's in therapy.

36:47.121 --> 36:48.246
Rocco?

36:51.834 --> 36:53.835
Are you serious?

36:54.003 --> 36:55.962
Who told you?

36:56.088 --> 36:58.965
Lele.
But don't say a word, okay?

37:00.718 --> 37:02.886
Whose phone is that? Mine?

37:03.763 --> 37:05.764
Who is it?

37:08.601 --> 37:10.227
- Steve Jobs.
- Who?

37:11.646 --> 37:15.023
- I thought he was dead.
- And why would he call my wife?

37:15.483 --> 37:17.609
- Darling!
- I'm coming!

37:17.985 --> 37:20.904
- It's urgent.
- Who is it? Mom?

37:21.530 --> 37:23.782
No... Steve Jobs.

37:25.618 --> 37:27.535
- Answer it.
- I don't speak English.

37:27.662 --> 37:29.913
Answer it! Don't be silly!

37:32.667 --> 37:35.043
- Hello, Riccardo.
- Good evening, Mrs. Masi.

37:35.169 --> 37:37.671
- Your computer's ready.
- Great.

37:37.797 --> 37:41.800
- How come you're working so late?
- Overtime, too many viruses about.

37:43.302 --> 37:47.055
I'll come get it tomorrow
around 7:00?

37:47.181 --> 37:50.058
- Sounds good.
- See you tomorrow.

37:50.935 --> 37:52.936
It's the computer guy.

37:53.062 --> 37:55.689
- And you call him "Steve Jobs"?
- Isn't it funny?

37:55.815 --> 37:58.692
And do you call the mechanic
"Marchionne"?

38:01.279 --> 38:05.699
- Text. One, two...
- Giulio for soccer.

38:06.200 --> 38:09.202
- Giulio soccer.
- Giulio, confirmed for tomorrow.

38:09.537 --> 38:11.955
- You were lucky.
- There's a game tomorrow?

38:14.458 --> 38:17.919
- Apparently.
- I didn't get a text.

38:18.963 --> 38:22.173
It'll come through,
it might just be a bit late.

38:22.550 --> 38:24.926
Is your phone out of minutes?

38:26.679 --> 38:30.849
- Have you kicked me off the team?
- No, Giulio just organized it...

38:30.975 --> 38:34.185
- You know what he's like.
- What is he like?

38:34.478 --> 38:37.105
- Absent-minded.
- Don't you know Giulio?

38:38.107 --> 38:41.234
Get your gym bag ready anyway.

38:41.360 --> 38:43.111
Yes, come anyway.

38:44.739 --> 38:48.867
You're such shits, you only include me
when you're short a goalie.

38:49.243 --> 38:53.371
- Do you really do that?
- That's not true.

38:53.748 --> 38:55.123
- Nonsense.
- Terrible!

38:55.583 --> 39:00.837
- Are you Alice in Wonderland?
- Why? If they're such good friends...

39:00.963 --> 39:04.132
Some friends! I didn't
get a message on WhatsApp.

39:05.259 --> 39:08.636
Turn it off then back on again,
sometimes...

39:08.763 --> 39:12.724
- He's right, sometimes...
- You're such shits.

39:14.602 --> 39:16.853
Message for Cosimo. Who is it?

39:18.856 --> 39:21.274
Marika.
"Call me, it's urgent."

39:21.650 --> 39:26.029
- Three exclamation points.
- Who's Marika, what's so urgent?

39:26.864 --> 39:29.157
- Who is she?
- The name sounds promising.

39:29.784 --> 39:33.661
Sorry to disappoint you, but
she's just the taxi company dispatcher.

39:35.164 --> 39:40.001
You know? "Go to Corso Rinascimento
in nine minutes."

39:40.127 --> 39:42.253
Call her back, I'm curious about her.

39:44.048 --> 39:48.009
We're eating and she might make me
fill in for someone.

39:48.135 --> 39:52.055
- Yes, a shift swap.
- Look at her defending her husband!

39:52.181 --> 39:56.684
- They haven't been married long!
- Darling, stick up for yourself.

39:57.937 --> 40:01.064
If I have to fill in for someone,
my weekend's ruined.

40:01.190 --> 40:05.193
- We're at my parents' on Sunday.
- Then she'll save your weekend.

40:09.198 --> 40:12.325
Anyway, Marika isn't his type.
She's a hick

40:12.701 --> 40:15.954
with tattoos and enormous boobs!

40:16.080 --> 40:19.165
What's her surname?
Perhaps I did her boob job.

40:23.170 --> 40:26.965
- It's mine, an American app.
- Can I see?

40:30.678 --> 40:33.430
- Where are you going?
- What is this?

40:33.806 --> 40:36.099
- An exercise program.
- What?

40:36.225 --> 40:40.478
It lasts 12 weeks

40:40.855 --> 40:43.731
and you can lose
from 8 to 12 kilos.

40:43.941 --> 40:47.360
- Guaranteed success.
- You only started today then!

40:47.486 --> 40:50.113
- Do you have to do it now?
- Whenever it pings.

40:50.448 --> 40:53.074
- Even at night?
- Yes, if it pings.

40:53.242 --> 40:55.869
- Then turn it off.
- I can't cheat.

40:56.078 --> 40:59.247
How can I teach P.E.
looking like this?

40:59.457 --> 41:02.959
Does the app know you ate half
a kilo of gnocchi in 30 seconds?

41:03.085 --> 41:05.462
- I'm burning them off.
- Dammit...

41:09.133 --> 41:14.220
That's brilliant. Where did
you find it? I want it too.

41:15.264 --> 41:18.892
- I downloaded it.
- Have you heard of it? I haven't.

41:19.018 --> 41:22.145
- On a full stomach.
- I swapped our phones.

41:23.022 --> 41:26.107
- Are you sure?
- Huh?

41:26.400 --> 41:28.735
- Are we sure?
- Don't bust my balls.

41:35.743 --> 41:37.744
Why didn't you tell me?

41:37.786 --> 41:40.413
- What?
- That you're in therapy.

41:40.748 --> 41:43.291
Why didn't you tell me?

41:47.004 --> 41:50.131
- I haven't been going long.
- How long?

41:50.758 --> 41:52.800
About six months.

41:52.927 --> 41:54.928
That's long enough.

41:56.138 --> 41:58.264
- Are you angry?
- No.

41:59.767 --> 42:01.392
Yes...

42:03.020 --> 42:05.063
I don't know, a bit.

42:06.273 --> 42:09.192
- You never wanted to before.
- I do now.

42:09.944 --> 42:12.445
You do now? Why?

42:12.780 --> 42:16.199
Maybe it is just a waste of time,
but I want to try everything.

42:17.451 --> 42:21.955
Then if we split up,
we can't say we didn't try.

42:26.293 --> 42:30.046
- And is it working?
- I don't know, you tell me.

42:40.307 --> 42:43.726
- But I've learnt something important.
- What's that?

42:44.853 --> 42:48.606
- How to defuse.
- Meaning?

42:48.941 --> 42:53.111
Not to turn every argument
into a fight for supremacy.

42:53.445 --> 42:57.323
I don't believe it's weak
to be the one to give in.

42:57.491 --> 42:59.617
In fact, I think it's wise.

42:59.994 --> 43:04.372
The only couples I see who last
are those where one of the two...

43:04.498 --> 43:08.334
manages to take a step back,
but is really a step ahead.

43:11.880 --> 43:16.009
I don't want us to end up like...
Barbie and Ken.

43:18.345 --> 43:21.264
You full of plastic
and me without any balls.

43:26.604 --> 43:31.024
- I'll change my shirt, it's sticky.
- Good idea.

43:42.786 --> 43:46.164
- The wine's good.
- WhatsApp for Peppe.

43:46.290 --> 43:49.542
- The only one who's not worried.
- It's a photo.

43:49.918 --> 43:51.919
From Isa Clementini.

43:52.046 --> 43:56.007
- Wait, it's not Lucilla!
- Why are you shouting?

43:56.133 --> 44:00.011
- To emphasize it.
- Isa Clementini sometimes sends me...

44:03.932 --> 44:05.266
You'll break it.

44:05.434 --> 44:07.685
- What's up?
- Nothing...

44:07.936 --> 44:09.937
- What is it?
- Can I have a look?

44:10.064 --> 44:12.940
- It's private.
- Everyone's sharing tonight.

44:13.400 --> 44:15.652
- Let us see.
- Show us or I'll get up...

44:17.196 --> 44:20.156
- Show us that photo.
- Get your hand off it!

44:20.324 --> 44:23.076
- Let go!
- Okay.

44:23.452 --> 44:26.162
Tonight everyone can look...

44:28.040 --> 44:30.416
Well I'll be damned, Peppe!

44:30.459 --> 44:32.710
- You chipped it.
- Let me see.

44:32.961 --> 44:36.339
- Just a sec!
- You have to see this.

44:36.674 --> 44:41.552
You're in the field, how do you...
Which way do you look at this?

44:41.679 --> 44:43.680
- Whose is it?
- Guess.

44:44.223 --> 44:47.183
- Looks like she's lying face down.
- Who is she?

44:47.351 --> 44:49.602
- It's not for you.
- What is it?

44:49.978 --> 44:51.437
No, no, no...

44:56.485 --> 44:58.611
Have you seen Peppe's girlfriend!

44:58.737 --> 45:02.365
She's not my girlfriend, do you
think I'd have a girlfriend like that?

45:02.491 --> 45:06.202
- She's doing pilates.
- No, the Sun Salutation.

45:08.455 --> 45:13.251
Peppe had no one for years after
his divorce, now girlfriends, lovers...

45:13.460 --> 45:17.004
You don't have to explain.
1 ,000 points for Peppe.

45:17.131 --> 45:20.341
- Yes, right.
- Hooray for Miss Clementini.

45:22.010 --> 45:24.470
What's that? A text?

45:24.638 --> 45:27.140
- Who got a text?
- You did.

45:27.266 --> 45:30.101
- It's mine, here.
- A frog ring tone?

45:30.269 --> 45:31.728
Who, me?

45:32.020 --> 45:35.773
Do you think I'm that stupid?
The kids must've done it.

45:36.525 --> 45:39.402
"How are you?"
How sweet...

45:40.154 --> 45:41.237
Who's Lucio?

45:41.405 --> 45:43.740
A co-worker from the legal office.

45:44.491 --> 45:47.744
- I don't remember him.
- You were on maternity leave.

45:47.995 --> 45:50.163
He's a nice guy.

45:50.539 --> 45:53.291
Why's he asking how you are?

45:53.417 --> 45:57.253
Because today I lost my temper
about that case in Basilicata

45:57.421 --> 45:59.130
that's been dragging on.

45:59.256 --> 46:00.673
He noticed I was a bit...

46:01.300 --> 46:03.509
- And you're not replying?
- No.

46:06.054 --> 46:10.183
I don't understand people
who don't answer texts.

46:10.559 --> 46:12.268
It won't take a second.

46:12.519 --> 46:17.190
This person was kind enough
to ask...

46:17.524 --> 46:21.569
All you have to say is,
"I'm fine, I'm at home."

46:21.695 --> 46:24.697
- That's right.
- Why? He's not at home.

46:26.408 --> 46:28.701
- That's right.
- I was just saying...

46:28.827 --> 46:33.664
Then write, "I'm fine, thanks.
I'm having dinner with friends."

46:33.791 --> 46:37.293
- That's right.
- Why must he say where he is?

46:39.588 --> 46:42.840
It's just a matter of principle.

46:43.175 --> 46:46.594
We don't have any privacy any more.
Once phone calls started with:

46:46.720 --> 46:49.597
"How are you?"
Now it's: "Where are you?"

46:50.182 --> 46:53.726
- No, he asked "how are you?"
- That's my business!

46:54.061 --> 46:57.480
Okay?
Why should I tell you where I am?

46:57.731 --> 47:00.858
Why?
And why the fuck would you care?

47:01.235 --> 47:05.446
- Why are you taking it out on me?
- These things are ruining our lives.

47:05.572 --> 47:08.115
They're taking our private lives
away from us.

47:08.325 --> 47:12.119
And we're allowing them to,
day after day, without realizing it.

47:17.125 --> 47:19.836
- Okay, I won't answer it.
- Good, don't answer it.

47:21.088 --> 47:24.257
Guys, this eclipse is having
a bad effect on you.

47:24.383 --> 47:26.717
Rocco, you've got an email.

47:27.636 --> 47:31.389
- I've got a text too.
- No, first Rocco's email.

47:31.515 --> 47:32.849
Scared?

47:33.642 --> 47:35.601
Scared of what?

47:35.644 --> 47:38.604
Orizzonti Tour.
The house in Salina's confirmed.

47:38.772 --> 47:41.524
- Thank goodness!
- You were lucky.

47:42.484 --> 47:45.403
Let's read Carlotta's text.

47:45.612 --> 47:48.656
No, I want to read one out.

47:49.783 --> 47:53.160
I've learnt something I want to...

47:53.370 --> 47:55.663
Siri, read email.

47:57.165 --> 47:59.166
You have no new email.

47:59.293 --> 48:01.794
Not even Siri understands you.
What email?

48:02.170 --> 48:04.297
- It's a message.
- A message.

48:05.382 --> 48:07.425
Siri, read the message.

48:10.512 --> 48:15.266
You have a message
from +393462371733.

48:15.392 --> 48:17.768
Dear Mrs. De Rosa,
we'd like to inform you

48:17.936 --> 48:20.187
we have a spot
available in June.

48:20.564 --> 48:24.525
During this time
we're offering a 25% discount.

48:24.693 --> 48:27.570
Do not hesitate to call us
for further information.

48:27.779 --> 48:31.824
Thank you for contacting us.
La Quiete Home for the Elderly.

48:33.785 --> 48:36.329
- Do you want to answer?
- I don't want to answer.

48:36.455 --> 48:39.415
Who sends messages at this hour?!
They're crazy!

48:39.583 --> 48:42.835
- La Quiete? Is it a rest home?
- No...

48:43.211 --> 48:47.340
I went there last week with
my friend Rita, her mom's there.

48:47.424 --> 48:51.218
It's lovely, I had a look around
and asked for some information.

48:51.345 --> 48:53.846
- That's all.
- That's all?

48:54.848 --> 48:57.183
You asked for information
at a rest home?

48:57.309 --> 49:02.563
That's like going to a funeral and
asking if there's a tomb available.

49:02.689 --> 49:05.358
It's not a rest home.
it's a five-star facility.

49:05.609 --> 49:07.234
So what?

49:07.444 --> 49:09.946
- Why didn't you tell me?
- I forgot.

49:10.364 --> 49:13.366
I didn't even save the number.

49:15.577 --> 49:17.620
I don't believe it.

49:17.746 --> 49:20.498
You want to kick mom out.

49:20.707 --> 49:24.710
Don't pass me off as something I'm not.
I'm not kicking anyone out.

49:24.878 --> 49:26.837
- That woman adores you.
- I know.

49:26.880 --> 49:29.632
She helps us out with the kids,
with everything.

49:30.258 --> 49:32.718
- Or am I mistaken?
- You're not mistaken, but...

49:32.886 --> 49:35.388
But what?

49:35.597 --> 49:39.850
I love her too, you know that.
But ever since she's been with us,

49:39.977 --> 49:42.853
our dynamics have changed.
Admit it.

49:44.898 --> 49:48.734
Sure... mom, who sleeps
in a cubicle at the end of the hall,

49:48.860 --> 49:52.405
is to blame for our problems.
Yes, that's possible.

49:52.781 --> 49:56.659
Pretend I never said anything.
We don't have problems, it's fine.

49:57.285 --> 50:02.415
I'm fond of Cosimo's mom too,
but if she came to live with us...

50:02.541 --> 50:05.292
I'm sorry, darling,
but I couldn't cope.

50:05.419 --> 50:08.921
With my mother? I wouldn't want
to live with her either.

50:09.297 --> 50:13.509
Some facilities are so nice
that old folks beg to go there.

50:13.677 --> 50:16.762
- It's like a resort.
- Did she tell you to say that?

50:16.888 --> 50:20.266
Would you live with Carlotta's mom?

50:20.308 --> 50:23.310
- My mother's a widow. Hers isn't.
- Mine isn't.

50:24.563 --> 50:29.817
Lele's right... but she can be a pain
in the ass when she wants to be.

50:31.278 --> 50:34.572
I got more slaps from your mom
than from my dad.

50:34.781 --> 50:38.325
- Obviously not enough.
- Your mom's not bursting with charm.

50:39.411 --> 50:43.164
Okay, I'll admit she can be
a bit difficult.

50:44.458 --> 50:47.334
- What time it is?
- Just after ten.

50:47.461 --> 50:49.587
- Let's go and see the eclipse.
- Yes!

50:49.796 --> 50:52.715
- Leave the phones on the table.
- Can I take mine? For a photo.

50:52.841 --> 50:56.343
- Okay, just you. Not you!
- Come on, the eclipse!

50:56.470 --> 50:59.930
They're well-organized.
As soon as they bury one,

51:00.057 --> 51:02.349
they send out a message
to find a replacement.

51:02.476 --> 51:07.104
- No joke, they were fully booked.
- I should open a nursing home.

51:07.481 --> 51:10.816
Open one in the hills.
Capers outside, old folks inside.

51:11.485 --> 51:14.320
It's lovely, though
I still see two of them.

51:14.696 --> 51:16.864
There are two,
one on top of the other.

51:19.451 --> 51:21.702
- Lovely, isn't it?
- Yes.

51:21.828 --> 51:24.622
It won't last much longer,
then it'll disappear.

51:24.831 --> 51:29.877
Listen, I'm sorry about before,
I said it without thinking.

51:30.003 --> 51:33.964
- I wouldn't want you to be upset.
- I'm not upset.

51:36.760 --> 51:40.888
I wonder why eclipses
fascinate us so much.

51:43.642 --> 51:46.894
- The Dark Side of the Moon!
- Great record!

51:53.026 --> 51:55.277
Let's take a photo, come over here.

51:56.404 --> 51:57.863
- Who'll take it?
- I will.

52:00.992 --> 52:03.661
- Squeeze together.
- I'll bend down or we won't fit.

52:03.870 --> 52:06.664
Wait, darling, I'll do it. Hold it...

52:06.915 --> 52:09.917
- Everyone in? Smile.
- One...

52:10.794 --> 52:12.253
"Hi".

52:14.506 --> 52:17.299
- What does he want on a Friday night?
- I don't know.

52:17.551 --> 52:18.676
- Who's Ivano?
- Her ex.

52:18.885 --> 52:21.011
- He's pissed.
- No.

52:21.388 --> 52:24.515
- I'm joking.
- Let's take the photo.

52:27.435 --> 52:31.814
- Why did you save his number as Ivano?
- How else? That's his name.

52:32.023 --> 52:34.525
- By his surname.
- Come on, he's her ex!

52:34.693 --> 52:36.569
- Precisely!
- Exes are dangerous.

52:36.778 --> 52:39.446
They're like the Japanese,
they never give up.

52:39.698 --> 52:41.407
Especially if they got dumped.

52:41.575 --> 52:43.826
That's right.
Bianca? Bianca?

52:44.911 --> 52:46.579
- Who broke it off?
- Me.

52:46.788 --> 52:48.914
Come on, take this photo.

52:49.082 --> 52:51.333
He's harmless,
but it's the principle...

52:51.459 --> 52:52.918
Smile!

52:54.045 --> 52:55.838
One, two...

52:55.964 --> 52:59.466
"I feel like screwing"

53:01.678 --> 53:05.181
- Good thing he was harmless.
- What the fuck?

53:05.223 --> 53:08.350
- I can explain.
- It says, "I feel like screwing"!

53:08.602 --> 53:11.687
- It could be predictive text.
- Shut the fuck up.

53:11.855 --> 53:13.856
- Let me explain.
- Go on then.

53:13.982 --> 53:18.110
Ivano's in a relationship
with this girl, it's all about sex.

53:18.236 --> 53:21.739
Well, it is for her but he's in love,

53:21.865 --> 53:24.575
but won't admit it
and he's suffering like a dog.

53:24.743 --> 53:28.078
- That's why he called the vet.
- Well?

53:29.748 --> 53:32.082
Well?
Why's he texting you?

53:33.251 --> 53:36.879
I don't know what's so funny.
What's so funny?

53:37.005 --> 53:42.760
- I tell you what, he can explain.
- No, there's really no need.

53:42.886 --> 53:47.014
Please, there's nothing to explain.
It's pointless, just stop.

53:47.641 --> 53:48.974
- All right?
- Quiet everyone.

53:53.772 --> 53:57.024
Hey, thanks for calling.
I'm sorry to be a pain, Bianca.

53:57.150 --> 53:59.151
- Did she call you?
- Yes.

53:59.778 --> 54:02.029
- And?
- She asked me over.

54:02.656 --> 54:05.032
- Don't go.
- I can't help myself.

54:05.158 --> 54:08.994
- She gets to me, I want to go.
- But she'll only hurt you.

54:09.246 --> 54:12.248
- I'm hurting enough as it is.
- It'll be worse if you go.

54:12.916 --> 54:16.919
- Some help you are!
- At least I'm trying to help.

54:17.295 --> 54:20.297
Otherwise don't bother calling,
you know what I think.

54:20.674 --> 54:24.051
- What a pain! Bye.
- Bye... Ivano!

54:24.427 --> 54:27.888
- Don't go there!
- Okay... bye.

54:30.809 --> 54:34.144
- Satisfied?
- How often do you talk?

54:34.437 --> 54:38.190
- Now and then.
- How often is now and then?

54:38.817 --> 54:41.318
- Every time he wants to...
- I get it.

54:41.528 --> 54:43.445
He panics and calls me.

54:44.906 --> 54:48.450
Give him Eva's number,
he needs a therapist, not an ex.

54:48.827 --> 54:51.954
- Guys, the meatloaf's ready.
- Unbelievable!

54:55.458 --> 54:59.420
- Why didn't you tell me you talk?
- Because it's not important.

54:59.796 --> 55:03.299
- There's nothing to tell.
- You say we should share everything.

55:03.425 --> 55:05.843
Everything that's important
for our relationship.

55:06.553 --> 55:10.973
- I think he still wants to screw you.
- And that seems very important.

55:11.099 --> 55:13.309
- Don't be silly!
- Yeah, don't be silly.

55:14.227 --> 55:18.230
- I don't talk to my exes.
- No, they'd prefer you dead.

55:18.356 --> 55:23.110
If it bothers you, I'll call him
and tell him not to call any more.

55:23.236 --> 55:26.238
- Right, you tell him.
- Then Cosimo is happy

55:26.364 --> 55:29.742
and you can speak to Ivano in secret.

55:29.868 --> 55:32.369
If I tell Cosimo I won't talk to him,
then I won't.

55:32.746 --> 55:36.874
Why shouldn't you talk to him?
He's a friend, Cosimo should trust you.

55:37.000 --> 55:39.877
I trust her, but I can't stand him.
Alright?

55:41.755 --> 55:46.383
- Doesn't Ivano have a house in Anzio?
- Yes, that's why she wanted to go.

55:46.593 --> 55:49.011
Yes, of course!

55:52.015 --> 55:55.392
- Does he really have a house there?
- You really are crazy!

55:55.518 --> 55:59.897
- I don't even know him!
- I'm not in the mood, Lele.

56:00.357 --> 56:02.399
I can see that.

56:04.402 --> 56:06.403
- It's Sofia.
- Answer it.

56:09.866 --> 56:13.410
- Hello, darling. Are you okay?
- Hi, dad. Yes, I'm fine.

56:13.912 --> 56:17.414
- Can you talk?
- Yes, of course. Go ahead.

56:17.749 --> 56:21.794
I don't know how to tell you this,
but Gregorio's parents are away.

56:21.920 --> 56:25.923
And he's asked me to go...
to sleep there.

56:27.884 --> 56:29.927
Dad, are you still there?

56:30.553 --> 56:34.181
- And what did you say?
- I don't know, I want to.

56:34.307 --> 56:37.434
But I wasn't expecting it tonight.

56:37.560 --> 56:40.813
If I don't go, he might be upset.
What shall I do?

56:41.022 --> 56:44.942
Don't go just because he'd be upset.
That can't be the only reason.

56:45.151 --> 56:47.194
Of course it's not...

